ðŸ’¡ Python Examples

# Convert decimal to binary, octal, hex
num = 20
print(bin(num))  # 0b10100 (binary)
print(oct(num))  # 0o24 (octal)
print(hex(num))  # 0x14 (hexadecimal)

# Convert back
print(int('10100', 2))  # 20 from binary
print(int('24', 8))     # 20 from octal
print(int('14', 16))    # 20 from hex




## ðŸ”„ Summary

| Number System | Base | Digits Used      | Power Positions     |
| ------------- | ---- | ---------------- | ------------------- |
| Binary        | 2    | 0,1              | 1, 2, 4, 8, 16...   |
| Octal         | 8    | 0â€“7              | 1, 8, 64, 512...    |
| Hexadecimal   | 16   | 0â€“9, A(10)â€“F(15) | 1, 16, 256, 4096... |

